00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,348
When you call producer.send(record), Kafka doesn't immediately write to the network.

2
00:00:05,298 --> 00:00:10,009
Instead: 1. Serialize key and value using configured serializers 2.

3
00:00:10,009 --> 00:00:14,596
Determine partition via key hash, round-robin, or custom Partitioner 3.

4
00:00:14,596 --> 00:00:20,105
Add to RecordAccumulator — an in-memory buffer organized by (topic, partition) 4.

5
00:00:20,105 --> 00:00:24,682
Batch sender thread drains the accumulator and sends batches to brokers 5.

6
00:00:24,682 --> 00:00:28,163
Await acknowledgment from the broker(s) per acks config 6.

7
00:00:28,163 --> 00:00:37,153
Callback is invoked with metadata (offset, partition, time Fun fact: Uber processes ride data in real-time — handling one billion events per day.

